segment.source: This topic lists AppLocker events and describes how to use Event Viewer with AppLocker.
segment.target: This topic lists AppLocker events and describes how to use Event Viewer with AppLocker.

segment.source: The AppLocker log contains information about applications that are affected by AppLocker rules.
segment.target: The AppLocker log contains information about applications that are affected by AppLocker rules.

segment.source: Each event in the log contains detailed info about:
segment.target: Each event in the log contains detailed info about:

segment.source: Which file is affected and the path of that file
segment.target: Which file is affected and the path of that file

segment.source: Which packaged app is affected and the package identifier of the app
segment.target: Which packaged app is affected and the package identifier of the app

segment.source: Whether the file or packaged app is allowed or blocked
segment.target: Whether the file or packaged app is allowed or blocked

segment.source: The rule type (path, file hash, or publisher)
segment.target: The rule type (path, file hash, or publisher)

segment.source: The rule name
segment.target: The rule name

segment.source: The security identifier (SID) for the user or group identified in the rule
segment.target: The security identifier (SID) for the user or group identified in the rule

segment.source: Review the entries in the Event Viewer to determine if any applications are not included in the rules that you automatically generated.
segment.target: Review the entries in the Event Viewer to determine if any applications are not included in the rules that you automatically generated.

segment.source: For instance, some line-of-business apps are installed to non-standard locations, such as the root of the active drive (for example: %SystemDrive%).
segment.target: For instance, some line-of-business apps are installed to non-standard locations, such as the root of the active drive (for example: %SystemDrive%).

segment.source: For info about what to look for in the AppLocker event logs, see Monitor app usage with AppLocker.
segment.target: For info about what to look for in the AppLocker event logs, see Monitor app usage with AppLocker.

segment.source: To review the AppLocker log in Event Viewer
segment.target: To review the AppLocker log in Event Viewer

segment.source: Open Event Viewer.
segment.target: Open Event Viewer.

segment.source: In the console tree under Application and Services LogsMicrosoftWindows, click AppLocker.
segment.target: In the console tree under Application and Services LogsMicrosoftWindows, click AppLocker.
